page.title: 01Laceby-a resume
page.content: Laceby is one of a number of 'spring-line'villages lying on the eastern edge of the Lincolnshire Wolds.It is about 3 miles west of Grimsby and has a population of just under 3,000.It is a thriving dormitory village of Grimsby and the Humber Bank Industries and the deep water port of Immingham are close by.For its size it has a good infrastructure with a well-stocked supermarket,a fish and chip shop,a Chinese takeaway,post office,two newsagents,an off-licence,three garages,an agricultual machine depot,an agricultural fertilizer depot,two churches,a bakery,clothes shop and greengrocers.Other than the shops and nearby farms there is no local employer of labour of any size.The locals are fighting hard to keep their village status.
